      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks!\nNetworkAdapter represents a physical network adapter\nhardware (e.g. Ethernet NICs, converged network\nadapters), mapping to the Redfish NetworkAdapter\nresource.\n\nbmcweb uses Item.NetworkAdapter as a D-Bus mapper\nfilter to expose the Redfish NetworkAdapter resource\ntree.\n\nExisting interfaces cannot substitute:\n- NetworkInterface is a logical network interface\n  (maps to Redfish EthernetInterface), not physical\n  network adapter hardware.\n- Board is too generic for bmcweb to distinguish\n  which objects are network adapters.\n- PCIeDevice describes PCIe identity — GPUs are also\n  PCIeDevice, so bmcweb cannot use it to distinguish\n  network adapters from other PCIe devices.\n\nThis interface follows the same pattern as\nFabricAdapter: an empty interface (no properties)\nwith a connecting association to Connector.Port.\n\nHow it is used:\n- dbus-sensors creates Item.NetworkAdapter on the\n  network adapter object and sets up a connecting\n  association to its Port objects.\n- bmcweb discovers all objects with\n  Item.NetworkAdapter via mapper query to expose\n  the Redfish NetworkAdapter collection, then follows\n  the connecting association to find Port objects.\n\nFull implementation:\nhttps://gerrit.openbmc.org/q/topic:\"CX_NetworkDeviceFunctions\"",
